**Blocking Issues**
[src/claude/watch-builder.ts:156] `shouldOutput` suppression skips `recordSpawn` because the loop `continue`s before lines 183-186 — nested subagents spawned from a parent whose output is suppressed, such as a pane-owned subagent, never enter `spawnRegistry`, so their children register as plain `[child]` instead of `[child◂parent]`.

[src/claude/subagent-detector.ts:607] parent lookup is a single immediate `spawnRegistry.get(meta.toolUseId)` after meta read — if the child file/meta is detected before the parent JSONL `tool_use` line is parsed and `recordSpawn` runs, the child is permanently registered without its parent label.

[src/claude/subagent-detector.ts:600] any queued FIFO description suppresses meta lookup and parent lookup — if a main-spawned agent was registered before its main JSONL line was parsed, that later `pushDescription` can become stale and be consumed by the next nested registration, causing wrong description and losing `[child◂parent]`.

